                                 )

In vitro studies using pooled sera from critically ill neonates have shown bumetanide to be a potent displacer of bilirubin (see 
      CLINICAL PHARMACOLOGY: Pediatric Pharmacology
   ). The administration of bumetanide could present a particular concern if given to critically ill or jaundiced neonates at risk for kernicterus.
